    feat(kanban-view): align board impl with spec/plan
    
    Replaces prior divergent implementation with spec-compliant version:
    
    - groupFeaturesByPhase: 6 phase buckets + defensive 'other' (FR-007, CON-009),
      partition invariant, all buckets init [] (CON-008). Replaces groupFeaturesByColumn
      which had a Backlog column and dropped unknown phases.
    - KanbanCard: new component with kanban-card-* testids, ring flags for
      gate_blocked (red) / waiting_for_human (yellow) (FR-011), local <span>
      question-badge to avoid nested anchors, gate text byte-identical to FeatureCard
      (CON-006).
    - badgeColors.ts: extracted shared statusColors map (CON-006). FeatureCard imports it.
    - useSessionView hook: sessionStorage-backed, Board default (FR-002/003),
      try/catch for private mode.
    - KanbanBoard: props-only, no useQuery (CON-007). Renders 6 phases + conditional
      'other'. Container h-[calc(100vh-8rem)] overflow-x-auto (FR-014/015).
    - KanbanColumn: w-60 (240px, FR-015), header fixed outside overflow-y-auto body
      (FR-013), 'No features' placeholder (FR-012).
    - Dashboard: single useQuery (CON-007), Board default via useSessionView,
      ViewToggle gated to !isLoading && !error && features.length > 0 (FR-004),
      loading/error/empty branches unchanged (FR-017, CON-008).
    - ViewToggle: added view-toggle container testid (AC-001).
    
    Existing kanban.spec.ts/kanban-api.spec.ts encode the prior (divergent)
    interpretation (Backlog column, feature-card-* testids on board, list default)
    and will fail against this spec-compliant impl; Tester owns test rewrite.
