## Verdict: BLOCKED — 2 Blocking findings

**Implementation source code is spec-compliant and minimal** (~257 lines across 7 files). All FR-001..FR-017 implemented. 18/22 ACs MET at code level. Constraint register CON-002/003/005/006/007/008 traced and satisfied.

**Blockers (config/test drift from re-alignment commit `6a7756d`):**

- **F-002 (Blocking)** — `ui/playwright.config.ts` default port regressed from `:18765` to `:8765` (CON-001 violation). Tests now target production port by default.
- **F-001 (Blocking)** — `ui/e2e/app.spec.ts` not updated for Board-default view. Existing `feature-card-*` assertions fail on `/` load because board cards emit `kanban-card-*`. Plan T-009 assigned this fixture; developer skipped it (CON-004 regression).

**Required:**
- **F-004** — AC-011 unit test + `vitest` devDep missing. `groupFeaturesByPhase` code is correct but unverified.
- **F-003** — `kanban.spec.ts` / `kanban-api.spec.ts` encode prior divergent impl (Backlog column, `feature-card-*` on board, `kanban-error` testid). Tester owns rewrite.

**Noted:** unused `PHASE_GROUP_KEYS` export (F-005), `kanban-error` testid mismatch (F-006, subsumed by F-003).

No security findings (view-only, no input/auth/mutation). No over-engineering. No language footguns. No null-safety issues (all buckets `[]`-init, `data?.features ?? []`). Cross-component consistency verified — `statusColors` single source in `badgeColors.ts`, both cards import; gate text byte-identical; `question-badge` testid reused without nested-anchor violation.

Not committing per reviewer discipline — pipeline handles pushes.
